f=Executive Office/echo/custom/pitch-framework/SKILL.md · in=pitch-framework turns fundraising partnership ask structured, investor-ready presentation either full slide deck underlying narrative/structure operator wants content. merges complete deck-building workflow separate source's slide-design content discipline, translated stripped any dependency specific paid external tool. · p=Give echo repeatable way "we need pitch" finished, professionally structured deck (or outline), matched actual audience purpose investor pitch, partnership proposal, customer demo without reinventing slide structure design judgment time. · wu=Triggers: "investor deck," "pitch update," "structure pitch," "fundraise narrative," "partnership proposal," "customer demo deck," converting existing `.ppt`/`.pptx` refreshed presentation. · st:/ Protocol=`Confirm mode (new deck / convert existing PPTX / refine existing HTML deck) \· -> Gather context (purpose, audience, length, content readiness) \· -> Select structure template matching the purpose \· -> Apply slide design discipline (framework, 1-6-6 rule, chart rules) \· -> Build self-contained output` · h3:Phase Confirm Mode=Ask which applies: · h3:Phase Confirm Mode=**New deck** operator topic, bullet points, full draft., **Convert existing** operator `.ppt`/`.pptx` file bring format., **Refine existing** operator already deck system wants improved. · h3:Phase Gather Context=Ask only what's necessary: · h3:Phase Gather Context=**Purpose**: investor pitch partnership proposal customer demo case review., **Audience**: investors potential partners customers internal team., **Length**: short (5-10 slides) medium (10-15) long (15-20, flag 20+ hurts attention)., **Content readiness**: full draft already written rough bullet points topic only. · h3:Phase Gather Context=operator already content, them paste before discussing style content first, presentation second. · h3:Phase Select Structure Template=Match purpose structure: **Investor Pitch** (target ~12 slides, minutes total): Title (company name, tagline) Problem (pain point, quantified data source) Solution (the product/service one sentence) Demo/Product (screenshot walkthrough) Market Size (TAM SAM SOM, shown concentric circles, pie chart) Business Model (how revenue made) Traction (growth metrics, customers, milestones up-and-to-the-right chart, numbers) Competition 2×2 positioning map, never feature-comparison table reads defensive) Team (max people; name, title, one relevant credential each) 10. Financials (revenue projections, unit economics) 11. Ask (amount, use funds, timeline) 12. Contact (next steps) **Partnership Proposal**: Title (proposal name, date) Context (why partner, now) Who (company summary, core strengths) Proposed structure (model, process) Mutual benefit (what partner specifically gains) Track record (relevant past results) Key terms (high-level, full contract) Next steps (clear call action) **Customer Demo Product Introduction**: Title (product name, core value proposition) Their pain point (scenario-based) Our solution (feature highlights) Proof (case studies data) Pricing (clear simple) FAQ Get started (call action) · h3:Phase Apply Slide Design Discipline=Regardless which template, slide follows: · h3:Phase Apply Slide Design Discipline=**The 1-6-6 rule**: idea slide, max words bullet, max bullets slide. text needed, add slide never shrink font fit., **Typography**: sans-serif only; title words; one key stat slide applicable; always cite data sources caption., **Color**: pick dark-background light-background commit whole deck; one accent color; max 2-3 colors any single chart; never gradients text., **Layout**: consistent margins; left-align body text (never centered); one visual slide; slide numbers., **Chart selection**: line chart growth over time, bar chart category comparisons, concentric circles TAM/SAM/SOM, 2×2 matrix competitive positioning, single big number key-metric highlight. **Never use pie chart** hard read, reads unprofessional. Start any Y-axis label directly chart rather relying separate legend., **What investor-pitch slide really answering** (keep mind while drafting content, design): Problem "is real worth paying solve?" Solution "is meaningfully better status quo?" Market "is big enough matter?" Traction "is actually working?" Team "can people execute?" Ask "is reasonable deal?" · h3:Phase 5 — Build=Output single self-contained file (inline CSS/JS, external dependencies) unless operator explicitly wants multi-file project: · h3:Phase 5 — Build=slide fits one viewport, internal scrolling content overflows, split another slide rather shrinking type., Include keyboard (arrow keys/space), touch/swipe, scroll-wheel navigation, plus progress indicator., Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`; keep any entrance animation purposeful, decorative sake., Use semantic HTML structure accessibility. · h3:Phase 5 — Build=converting existing `.ppt`/`.pptx`: extract slide titles, body text, speaker notes, images first (see Fallback extraction script), preserve slide order speaker notes, proceed through Phase onward extracted content. · h3:Phase 6 — Deliver=Summarize what produced: file path/name, structure template used, slide count, any content gaps flagged rather guessed at. · h2:Common Mistakes Flag (in review, self-check before delivering)=many slides (20+) loses attention; cap around 12-15., Wall text apply 1-6-6 rule., Feature-comparison table against competitors looks defensive; use 2×2 positioning map instead., Pie charts — never., cited data sources looks fabricated., Team slide people unfocused; cap relevant only., Inconsistent design across slides colors/fonts/margins throughout., "Ask" slide investor pitch state amount, use funds, timeline explicitly., Vanity metrics ("1M visits" conversion context) show revenue, active users, retention instead., Over-indexing product demo business pitch, product tour; cap product-focused slides · pr=Content before style never start visual design before actual narrative/content settled., fabricated data sources number isn't provided, flag missing rather inventing plausible one., One committed visual direction deck don't mix styles slide slide., Never solve overflow shrinking text below readable size split slides instead., generated deck run standalone browser external service dependency. · f=**PPTX conversion script built.** source skill merged includes `scripts/pptx_extract.py`-style tool pulling slide titles, body text, speaker notes, image paths out existing `.pptx` file. script built tested pass (it wasn't discussed/approved build process) flag operator rather claiming capability exists. Until it's built, `.pptx` needs converting, ask operator paste content manually, raise building extraction script separate discussion first., operator doesn't know their audience purpose yet, don't guess template ask, since wrong structure (e.g. investor structure customer demo) undermines whole pitch., content genuinely incomplete (e.g. traction data yet), say explicitly delivered output rather filling gap placeholder looks like real data. · b:with Other echo Skills=pitch-framework produces deck/narrative structure; `investor-update-generator` (marketplace) checks investor *update* against best practices different artifact (recurring update vs. one-off pitch)., canonical pitch story skill draws stay consistent whatever `pitch-narrative` (custom, built) maintains versioned narrative source truth, once skill exists.